<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-CCC0DD09-2C61-40BF-A40B-1EA7F577AD3D" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-CCC0DD09-2C61-40BF-A40B-1EA7F577AD3D" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">11 How to do a system software installation on a non-empty disk (new system installation)</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M140828-B205"><p class="- topic/p ">In case the system is installed and new software is directly required use the following procedure. 
</p><note class="- topic/note " id="GUID-8FFD5F6C-26E6-4A97-8F97-58210F7D8170"><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="SoftwareTypes" href="GUID-4A3BEFEB-96F5-4931-A8B5-F279F0389248.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text What are the different software types?>11 What are the different software types</xref> for version and release descriptions. 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="M140828-B207" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph ">Required tools</ph></title><ul id="UL_722C828A7C8B49C38ED1C503C2455D18" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_762E1C1CD22645E18F423FA4CA460DC0" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> A prepared USB install key with the software version that you want to install. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If you already have one make sure you used the reactivation instruction . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For both instructions see : 
<xref keyref="20INST-USBKEY" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-51DC0123-5924-4D7D-B345-F3B06B4B248C.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to create an Océ Colorado 1640  installation USB Key?>11 How to create an installation USB Key</xref>. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="M140828-B208" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><note id="M140828-NOE211" type="note" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">This procedure takes approximately 45 minutes. 
</p></note></section><section id="SECTION_8B2EDF5F2405440097F73F1429FA79F0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Upgrade the system software</title><p class="- topic/p ">All time indications are approximately. 
</p><table id="GUID-44E51CAE-2EF5-431B-BFBB-AE0F0810C645" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" align="left" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Insert the installation USB key in the USB port located close to the printer operator panel 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Power the printer on. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The system software installation is then performed without user intervention. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Main steps are described hereafter. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The USB key is detected by the system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following message displays on the printer operator panel: 
</p><fig id="GUID-066A22C3-82DB-4111-AD40-2F746AF708CB" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EA96EE0A-FFF1-4229-857B-862F11818B3A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EA96EE0A-FFF1-4229-857B-862F11818B3A-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The system checks the software files integrity. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following message displays repetitively: 
</p><fig id="GUID-7F65F6A1-9118-4D70-9992-5D2E3BBA78E4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-921ADA49-3793-45A0-8B07-E8FE712561E7-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-921ADA49-3793-45A0-8B07-E8FE712561E7-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 minutes after the installation started, the software files are copied from the USB key to the Windows controller. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following message displays repetitively: 
</p><fig id="GUID-A34B5760-89B6-47D5-8B53-63B34FE6F3BB" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-247E0879-B670-459F-BA50-7884A77D2552-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-247E0879-B670-459F-BA50-7884A77D2552-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 minutes after the installation started, the copy process completes. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The printer reboots automatically. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following window displays on the printer operator panel: 
</p><fig id="GUID-631A13E5-54C2-41FB-A082-5A94E34FF879" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4CDF19C1-1BD3-405A-9F82-43FB2B71FD39-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4CDF19C1-1BD3-405A-9F82-43FB2B71FD39-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Then the installation progress wheel displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-263CF450-B09C-4D0F-BA40-80E92F849E72" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-653F0B23-6779-485F-A851-0DBF4421ED57-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-653F0B23-6779-485F-A851-0DBF4421ED57-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">18 minutes after the installation started, 40% of the installation process completed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The printer reboots and its configuration starts. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following messages display: 
</p><fig id="GUID-DCA9D51F-88E5-47D0-B5C0-7FC320FA7913" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D7AAEDFA-A4BD-4888-B587-2266AF2F8181-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D7AAEDFA-A4BD-4888-B587-2266AF2F8181-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Then, 
</p><fig id="GUID-B803CE36-3D39-422A-8AF0-F822FD3B9ABF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-01ABE778-75D0-4A9C-A9D0-1888B008C4BD-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-01ABE778-75D0-4A9C-A9D0-1888B008C4BD-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">21 minutes after the installation started, the printer automatically reboots. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The Finalizing your settings message displays, then replaced by installation progress wheel: 
</p><fig id="GUID-ACAB1352-360C-4D31-BDA3-53AD546F07B9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-299C68B4-0371-4EF6-8AB8-5B9E76D70FCF-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-299C68B4-0371-4EF6-8AB8-5B9E76D70FCF-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The installation completes 35 minutes after it started. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The printer reboots. 
</p></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">40 minutes after the installation started, the following message displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-80DFBE9C-EE77-46D1-84CB-33AED13CB8C4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-679909BB-1038-42A4-AAB5-0B93E40C5F85-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-679909BB-1038-42A4-AAB5-0B93E40C5F85-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the USB key from the USB port 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-724C7F1C-09E3-4D8F-B77B-2B159E768314.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>